parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt webbing can lead to a loss of restraint, increasing the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seat belt webbing is weathered
frayed
or broken
causing the seat belt to malfunction or not stay engaged.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt buckle can cause the seat belt to not stay engaged, increasing the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seat belt buckle will not stay latched
the seat belt will not retract
or the seat belt buckle is faulty.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt retractor can cause the seat belt to not retract properly, increasing the risk of injury or entrapment.
symptoms: The seat belt retractor does not retract
or the retractor malfunctions
causing the seat belt to not function properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the dealer to handle the recall can lead to a delay in repairing the faulty seat belt component, increasing the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The dealer is unaware of the recall
or refuses to handle the recall
causing a delay in repairing the faulty seat belt component.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to shut down while driving, leading to a loss of control and potential accidents. It can also cause instrument panel malfunctions, making it difficult for the driver to access important information.
symptoms: Vehicle shuts down while driving
instrument panel is inoperative
failure to start the vehicle without jump-starting.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause an electrical short, leading to a fire in the engine compartment, even when the vehicle is parked. This can result in damage to the vehicle and potentially cause injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Engine compartment fire
electrical short
failure of ignition switch.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the instrument panel can make it difficult for the driver to access important information, such as speed, fuel level, and warning lights, which can lead to accidents or other safety issues.
symptoms: Instrument panel is inoperative
failure of individual gauges or warning lights.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The lack of a secure wheel retention system can cause the wheels to come loose or fall off while driving, leading to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Wheels come loose or fall off while driving
lug nuts or bolts break off
wheels detach from the vehicle
difficulty steering or controlling the vehicle.
